# Accessibility Rules (WCAG 2.1 AA)

## Contrast
- Body text: **4.5:1** minimum contrast against its background.
- Large text (24px+ / 19px+ bold): **3:1** minimum.
- Verify both light and dark themes meet these ratios.

## Forms & controls
- Every `<input>`, `<select>`, and `<textarea>` has an associated `<label>`
  (via `for`/`id`), never placeholder-only labelling.
- Every `<button>` has discernible text or an `aria-label`.

## Keyboard
- All interactive elements are reachable and operable with the keyboard
  (Tab to move, Enter/Space to activate, Escape to dismiss overlays).
- Logical, source-order focus flow. No keyboard traps.

## Focus visibility
- Visible focus indicators via `:focus-visible`.
- Never `outline: none` without providing an equivalent visible replacement.

## Icons
- Icon-only controls MUST have an `aria-label` or a visually hidden
  `<span class="sr-only">`.
- Decorative SVGs use `aria-hidden="true"` and `focusable="false"`.

## ARIA discipline
- Use `role` and `aria-*` ONLY when no native HTML semantic exists.
- Prefer native elements (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`) over ARIA roles.

## Touch targets
- Minimum interactive target size **44×44px**.

## Motion
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` for ALL animations and transitions.
- Provide a non-animated fallback state (content visible without motion).

## Images
- `alt=""` for purely decorative images.
- Meaningful, concise `alt` text for content images.

## Landmarks (every page)
- Exactly one `<header>`, one `<main>`, one `<footer>`.
- Primary navigation as `<nav aria-label="Primary">`.
- A skip-to-content link as the first focusable element.
